10mm undead knights for Warmaster. Five plus one strips, three regular knights and two command ones. I added a wight lord as well and a command strip with him as the unit champion. The wight lord is a fantastic design, I could not not include him.

I broke the tail of one of the horses while removing the supports. I think that is the weakest part, you might want to watch out there. It seems strong enough when cured though. I have not painted them yet, I hope they will survive my violent drybrushing.

Description :

Five strips of 10mm skeletons for Warmaster. One command strip and four regular ones. Oh man, this was such a fun project! I wanted to have a similar chaotic feel to the strips as the original Citadel miniatures. I probably did not achieve that, but it is definiately not as well organized as my skeletons for example. I am not sure whether the more unique guys stick out if you print more units, but none of the zombies are merged with the strip, so you can easily remove those or the scenery.

Source for the HeroQuest zombie: https://www.myminifactory.com/object/3d-print-heroquest-zombie-resculpt-82522

Five strips of 10mm skeletons for Warmaster. One command strip and four regular ones. I also uploaded my first quick concept sketch, so actually six strips - a whole unit. I sculpted the skulls for the concept really fast, and even though they look a bit silly, I like them a lot.

I decided to follow the original GW layout, so there are seven warriors per strip. There are only 14 different poses though, and I learned something new while making them as well. Posing skeletons is fun.

Other sources used:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/various/heroic-scale-skull-28mm

The generated assets:
https://www.meshy.ai/3d-models/Skull-Emblem-Shield-v2-01991b30-aead-7426-ba83-cb0840bce9d4
https://www.meshy.ai/3d-models/Skull-Banner-v2-01991be5-e1c4-7aa2-a664-20082d086ddf (used my quick sketch to generate it - worked OK, even though I don't really like the results of Meshy now)

I have not testprinted them yet, I hope the legs are sturdy enough.
